The paper proposes a generative model that leverages variational inference and deep learning techniques to infer spillover effects between pairs of entities. This involves treating latent attributes as confounders that affect both the treatment and outcome of units. The paper uses datasets from job training and e-commerce domains to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed model. Given these characteristics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves causal inference, which could place it in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
